{
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Lars Demo Video - IJCAI-ECAI 2026",
    "version": "1.0",
    "total_duration_seconds": 600,
    "resolution": "1920x1080",
    "fps": 30,
    "language": "en"
  },
  "scenes": [
    {
      "id": "scene_01_intro",
      "name": "Introduction",
      "duration_seconds": 45,
      "segments": [
        {
          "id": "01_01",
          "start_time": 0,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Evaluating Large Language Model outputs requires two groups with complementary expertise: Domain experts who understand what constitutes quality, and AI developers who know how to structure effective prompts.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "title_slide",
            "content": {
              "title": "Lars",
              "subtitle": "A Platform for Evaluating LLM Outputs with Human and Machine Evaluators",
              "authors": "Philipp Steigerwald, Jens Albrecht",
              "affiliation": "Technische Hochschule Nürnberg"
            }
          },
          "actions": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01_02",
          "start_time": 15,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Current tools force these groups to work in isolation. Annotation platforms lack LLM integration, while LLM evaluation frameworks require technical expertise.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "diagram",
            "content": "problem_statement_diagram"
          },
          "actions": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01_03",
          "start_time": 30,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Lars bridges this gap with three integrated modules: Collaborative Prompt Engineering, Batch Generation, and Large-Scale Evaluation. Let me show you how they work together.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "url": "http://localhost:55080"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "navigate", "url": "http://localhost:55080", "wait_for": "element", "selector": ".v-app"}
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "scene_02_prompt_engineering",
      "name": "Collaborative Prompt Engineering",
      "duration_seconds": 135,
      "segments": [
        {
          "id": "02_01",
          "start_time": 45,
          "duration": 10,
          "narration": "Let's start with Collaborative Prompt Engineering. Here, domain experts and AI developers work together in real-time to develop evaluation prompts.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "sidebar_prompt_engineering"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-prompt-engineering']", "wait_for": "navigation"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 1500}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "02_02",
          "start_time": 55,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "I'll create a new prompt for news article summarization. Watch how changes are tracked at the character level - every edit shows who made it and when.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "create_prompt_button"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='create-prompt-btn']", "wait_for": "modal"},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='prompt-name-input']", "text": "News Summary Prompt", "delay": 50},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='create-confirm-btn']", "wait_for": "element", "wait_selector": ".prompt-editor"}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "02_03",
          "start_time": 70,
          "duration": 25,
          "narration": "The system block defines the LLM's role. As a journalist, I specify that summaries must be exactly two sentences, factually accurate, and written in neutral tone. Notice how each block is editable with full version control.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "system_block"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='block-system']"},
            {"type": "clear", "selector": "[data-testid='block-system-content']"},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='block-system-content']", "text": "You are an expert news editor creating concise summaries for busy readers.\nYour summaries must be:\n- Exactly 2 sentences long\n- Factually accurate (no hallucinations)\n- Include the key finding and its significance\n- Written in neutral, journalistic tone", "delay": 30}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "02_04",
          "start_time": 95,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "The user block contains variables in double curly braces. These placeholders - title, category, content - will be filled with actual data during batch generation.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "user_block"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='block-user']"},
            {"type": "clear", "selector": "[data-testid='block-user-content']"},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='block-user-content']", "text": "Summarize this news article:\n\nTitle: {{title}}\nCategory: {{category}}\n\nArticle:\n{{content}}", "delay": 30}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "02_05_collab",
          "start_time": 115,
          "duration": 25,
          "narration": "Now watch real-time collaboration in action. In this second browser window, another team member - let's say our AI developer Max - joins the same prompt. Both cursors are visible, and edits synchronize instantly through conflict-free replicated data types.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "split_screen",
            "left": "browser_user_1",
            "right": "browser_user_2"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "switch_window", "window": 2},
            {"type": "navigate", "url": "http://localhost:55080/prompt-engineering", "wait_for": "element", "selector": ".prompt-list"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='prompt-item-1']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 1000},
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": ".collaborator-cursor", "duration": 3000},
            {"type": "switch_window", "window": 1}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "02_06_test",
          "start_time": 140,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "Each user can test the prompt independently without blocking others. I'll upload a sample article and immediately see how the LLM interprets our criteria. This tight feedback loop enables rapid iteration.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "test_panel"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='test-prompt-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 500},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='test-input-title']", "text": "Breakthrough in Quantum Computing", "delay": 30},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='test-input-content']", "text": "Scientists at MIT announced a major breakthrough...", "delay": 20},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='run-test-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait_for", "selector": "[data-testid='test-output']", "timeout": 10000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "02_07_version",
          "start_time": 160,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "The version history tracks every change. We can compare versions, see who contributed what, and roll back if needed. This is valuable for compliance documentation under regulations like the EU AI Act.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "version_history"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='version-history-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 1500},
            {"type": "scroll", "selector": ".version-list", "direction": "down", "amount": 200},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='close-history-btn']"}
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "scene_03_batch_generation",
      "name": "Batch Generation",
      "duration_seconds": 90,
      "segments": [
        {
          "id": "03_01",
          "start_time": 180,
          "duration": 10,
          "narration": "With our prompt refined, let's move to Batch Generation. This module bridges prompt engineering and evaluation by automating output creation at scale.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "sidebar_batch_generation"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-batch-generation']", "wait_for": "navigation"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 1500}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "03_02",
          "start_time": 190,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "I'll create a new generation job. The system generates all combinations of evaluation items, prompt templates, and LLM models - a matrix approach for systematic comparison.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "create_job_button"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='create-job-btn']", "wait_for": "modal"},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='job-name-input']", "text": "News Summary Comparison", "delay": 50}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "03_03",
          "start_time": 205,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "First, I upload our five news articles as the data source. The system detects the fields automatically - title, content, category - matching our prompt variables.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "data_source_panel"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='source-type-upload']"},
            {"type": "upload_file", "selector": "[data-testid='file-upload']", "file": "data/news_articles.json"},
            {"type": "wait_for", "selector": "[data-testid='field-mapping']", "timeout": 3000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "03_04",
          "start_time": 225,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Next, I select our News Summary Prompt and choose three LLM models: Mistral-Small for speed, GPT-4 as our quality reference, and Claude-Haiku as an alternative.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "model_selection"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='prompt-select']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='prompt-option-1']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='model-mistral-small']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='model-gpt4']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='model-claude-haiku']"}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "03_05",
          "start_time": 240,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Before execution, Lars estimates the total cost based on token counts and model pricing. I can set budget limits - jobs automatically pause if costs exceed thresholds.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "cost_estimation"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='cost-estimate']", "duration": 3000},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='budget-limit']", "text": "5.00", "delay": 100}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "03_06",
          "start_time": 255,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Starting the job - watch the real-time progress via WebSocket. Five articles times three models equals fifteen outputs. Each result maintains full provenance: source item, prompt, and model.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "progress_panel"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='start-job-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait_for", "selector": "[data-testid='job-progress']", "timeout": 2000},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 8000, "note": "Wait for some outputs to complete"}
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "scene_04_evaluation",
      "name": "Large-Scale Evaluation",
      "duration_seconds": 150,
      "segments": [
        {
          "id": "04_01",
          "start_time": 270,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Now for Large-Scale Evaluation. I'll convert our generated outputs directly into an evaluation scenario. The AI-assisted Scenario Wizard analyzes the data and suggests the appropriate evaluation type.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "to_scenario_button"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='to-scenario-btn']", "wait_for": "modal"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 2000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "04_02",
          "start_time": 285,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "The wizard detected that we have multiple summaries per article from different models. It recommends Ranking - asking evaluators which summary is best. This makes sense: relative comparison is easier for humans than absolute scores.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "wizard_recommendation"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='suggested-type']", "duration": 2000},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='evaluation-type-ranking']"},
            {"type": "type", "selector": "[data-testid='scenario-name']", "text": "News Summary Evaluation", "delay": 50}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "04_03",
          "start_time": 305,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "I configure bucket-based ranking with three tiers: Best, Acceptable, and Poor. Evaluators first sort summaries into buckets, then rank within each bucket - reducing cognitive load for large-scale evaluations.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "bucket_config"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='bucket-config-btn']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='bucket-preset-3']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='create-scenario-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait_for", "selector": "[data-testid='scenario-created']", "timeout": 5000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "04_04",
          "start_time": 320,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "Here's the evaluation interface. Each article appears with its three candidate summaries. Evaluators drag and drop to rank them. The interface is designed for domain experts - no technical knowledge required.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "evaluation_interface"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-evaluation']", "wait_for": "navigation"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='scenario-card-1']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 1500},
            {"type": "drag_drop", "source": "[data-testid='item-2']", "target": "[data-testid='bucket-best']"},
            {"type": "drag_drop", "source": "[data-testid='item-1']", "target": "[data-testid='bucket-acceptable']"},
            {"type": "drag_drop", "source": "[data-testid='item-3']", "target": "[data-testid='bucket-poor']"}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "04_05_llm_judge",
          "start_time": 340,
          "duration": 25,
          "narration": "Human evaluation is the gold standard, but domain experts' time is limited. That's why Lars supports LLM evaluators running in parallel. I'll add GPT-4 as an LLM judge using the same ranking criteria. Watch how both human and machine evaluations proceed simultaneously.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "llm_evaluator_panel"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='scenario-settings-btn']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='enable-llm-eval']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='llm-model-select']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='llm-option-gpt4']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='start-llm-eval-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 3000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "04_06_agreement",
          "start_time": 365,
          "duration": 25,
          "narration": "The real power is in the live agreement dashboard. Lars computes agreement across all evaluator combinations in real-time: human-human for inter-annotator reliability, LLM-LLM for model consistency, and critically, human-LLM alignment. Here we see Krippendorff's alpha, Cohen's kappa, and correlation coefficients updating as evaluations come in.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "agreement_dashboard"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-dashboard']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 1500},
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='agreement-matrix']", "duration": 4000},
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='krippendorff-alpha']", "duration": 3000},
            {"type": "scroll", "selector": ".dashboard-content", "direction": "down", "amount": 300}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "04_07_insights",
          "start_time": 390,
          "duration": 30,
          "narration": "The dashboard immediately reveals insights. In this case, GPT-4 tends to prefer longer summaries while human evaluators value conciseness. This disagreement pattern - visible in real-time - tells us exactly where to focus our next iteration. We can return to prompt engineering with these insights and refine our criteria until alignment improves.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "disagreement_analysis"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='disagreement-tab']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 2000},
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='disagreement-chart']", "duration": 5000}
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "scene_05_standalone",
      "name": "Standalone Use Cases",
      "duration_seconds": 90,
      "segments": [
        {
          "id": "05_01",
          "start_time": 420,
          "duration": 15,
          "narration": "Each module also works independently. Let me show you standalone use cases. First, Batch Generation without evaluation - useful for creating synthetic training data or test datasets.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "batch_generation"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-batch-generation']", "wait_for": "navigation"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='job-item-1']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='export-btn']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='export-csv']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 2000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "05_02",
          "start_time": 435,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "Second, evaluation without batch generation. I can import existing outputs from any source - production systems, competitor analyses, research datasets. Here I'll upload a CSV with pre-generated summaries from an external system.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "import_external"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-scenarios']", "wait_for": "navigation"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='create-scenario-btn']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='import-external-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 1000},
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='import-dialog']", "duration": 3000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "05_03",
          "start_time": 455,
          "duration": 20,
          "narration": "And third, prompt engineering as a standalone training environment. Organizations use this workspace to document prompt development decisions with full attribution - relevant for compliance and knowledge transfer.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "prompt_workspace"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-prompt-engineering']", "wait_for": "navigation"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='prompt-item-1']"},
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='export-json-btn']"},
            {"type": "wait", "duration": 2000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "05_04",
          "start_time": 475,
          "duration": 35,
          "narration": "The modular design means teams can adopt Lars incrementally. Start with evaluation for an existing project, add batch generation when you need scale, and bring in collaborative prompt engineering when domain experts join the team.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "diagram",
            "content": "modular_adoption_diagram"
          },
          "actions": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "scene_06_results",
      "name": "Results & Impact",
      "duration_seconds": 60,
      "segments": [
        {
          "id": "06_01",
          "start_time": 510,
          "duration": 30,
          "narration": "In our deployment evaluating counseling responses, this workflow improved human-LLM agreement by 12 percent over four weeks. Five psychology students and two LLM evaluators collected 2,400 ratings. The live agreement metrics helped us identify systematic biases and iterate on our prompts until criteria were properly captured.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "browser",
            "highlight": "results_visualization"
          },
          "actions": [
            {"type": "click", "selector": "[data-testid='nav-dashboard']", "wait_for": "navigation"},
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='correlation-chart']", "duration": 5000},
            {"type": "highlight", "selector": "[data-testid='improvement-metric']", "duration": 5000}
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "06_02",
          "start_time": 540,
          "duration": 30,
          "narration": "The key insight: domain experts know what matters but struggle to express it in prompts. AI developers can write effective prompts but lack domain knowledge. Lars brings both groups into a shared environment where they iterate together until criteria are properly captured and validated at scale.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "diagram",
            "content": "collaboration_impact"
          },
          "actions": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "scene_07_conclusion",
      "name": "Conclusion",
      "duration_seconds": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "id": "07_01",
          "start_time": 570,
          "duration": 30,
          "narration": "Lars is open-source under MIT license. It requires Docker, 16 gigabytes of RAM, and supports over 100 LLM providers through LiteLLM. Visit our repository to get started, and find us at the demo booth to try it yourself. Thank you for watching.",
          "visual": {
            "type": "end_slide",
            "content": {
              "title": "Try Lars",
              "repository": "github.com/llars-project/llars",
              "documentation": "llars-project.github.io",
              "requirements": ["Docker 20.10+", "16GB RAM", "4+ CPU cores"],
              "license": "MIT"
            }
          },
          "actions": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
